  '<h3 id="http-client-redirect">b.httpClient.request({ maxRedirects }) <a class="anchor" href="#http-client-redirect">#</a></h3>',
  '<p>Pass <code>maxRedirects: N</code> to follow up to N hops. Without the opt, 3xx responses still throw as <code>HTTP_ERROR</code>. The SSRF gate runs at every hop; <code>Authorization</code> / <code>Cookie</code> / <code>Proxy-Authorization</code> headers strip on cross-origin hops; 303 always coerces follow-up to GET; 307/308 preserve method + body.</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">var reqShape = { url: "https://short.ly/abc", maxRedirects: 5 };',
  '// var res = await b.httpClient.request(reqShape);',
  'b.httpClient.request;</code></pre>',

  '<h3 id="http-client-multipart">b.httpClient.request({ multipart }) <a class="anchor" href="#http-client-multipart">#</a></h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  fields:         { <name>: string | [string] },',
  '  files:          [{ field, filename, contentType, content }],',
  '}</code></pre>',
  '<p>Round-trip parity with <code>b.middleware.bodyParser({ multipart: ... })</code>. The framework builds the body with a random boundary; method defaults to POST. Buffers, strings, or <code>Readable</code> streams accepted as <code>content</code>.</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">var reqShape = {',
  '  url: "https://upstream/upload",',
