  '<p>RFC 6265 jar for multi-call flows where outbound cookies need to persist across requests — login → mutate → logout, OAuth code-exchange → userinfo, etc. <code>persist: "vault"</code> seals every cookie value via <code>b.vault.seal</code> so a memory dump or core file never exposes plaintext cookie state. Attribute coverage: Domain (with subdomain match), Path (prefix match), Expires / Max-Age (Max-Age wins on conflict), HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite.</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">var jar = b.httpClient.cookieJar.create({ persist: "memory" });',
