  '<p>Outbound signer — produces the Stripe-shape header <code>t=&lt;sec&gt;,id=&lt;uuid&gt;,&lt;kid&gt;=&lt;sig&gt;</code> for a payload. Multi-key rotation works the same way as JWT — keep old <code>kid</code>s in the signer map until you\'re sure no in-flight delivery is signed by them. Returns an instance with <code>sign(payload)</code>, <code>headers(payload)</code>, and <code>send(opts)</code> (which composes <code>b.httpClient</code> + <code>b.retry</code> internally).</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">var s = b.webhook.signer({',
